https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gr%C5%93nl: Grœnlendinga þáttr ('The Tale of the Greenlanders') or Einars þáttr Sokkasonar ('The Tale of Einarr Sokkason') is a short medieval Icelandic tale (þáttr).[1] It is preserved in the manuscript Flateyjarbók, towards the end of the second half of the manuscript which was written by Magnús Þórhallsson.[1] The author of the tale itself is unknown.[1] The tale takes place in Greenland, and unlike Grœnlendinga þáttr (I), it makes no mention of Vinland.
